<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Nicely written. Good info too. *NT*</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Gray Rage (DB)">Gray Rage (DB)</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 4:47 p.m. 26/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Nicely written. Good info too. *NT*<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1166" TARGET=_self>Druid reign supreme in 1v1......(txt)</A> (Angus[CC])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Druids rule 1v1, they are the most well rounded class. This

<BR>&gt; means that of all the major skills/stats they are pretty good if
<BR>&gt; not at least average at everything. example: Hit points - They
<BR>&gt; have higher HP than all other casting classes, Melee - They are
<BR>&gt; actually able to defend themsleves with melee weapons
<BR>&gt; effectively, this is mainly a bonus at lower levels till about
<BR>&gt; 14th, Spell casting - They have a extremely diverse spell
<BR>&gt; portfolio, and can deal damage and heal - this combination alone
<BR>&gt; places them at the top of the heap. To be able to heal as well
<BR>&gt; as they do makes them damn near unstoppable if the player knows
<BR>&gt; what he's doing 1v1 at least.
<P>&gt; Now as far as group fights go, you will need a diverse group to
<BR>&gt; be the victor, and the balances shift at higher levels. A wizard
<BR>&gt; after level 20 can lay some serious ass whoop down with VERY
<BR>&gt; high damage spells. Wizards are second to none for sheilding
<BR>&gt; spells, leather skin makes the difference at higher levels. I
<BR>&gt; believe that due to this one spell the Wizard will be king PvP
<BR>&gt; 1v1 after level 20.
<P>&gt; As far as races go for each of these classes I would have to say
<BR>&gt; Halfling for druid and Erudite for Wizard. Halfing is a clearly
<BR>&gt; better race for druids, but Erudites have only a mild advantage
<BR>&gt; in Int and Agil combo for wizards, Both Dark Elf and Gnome are
<BR>&gt; EXTREMELY viable for wizards with High elf pulling up a close
<BR>&gt; 3rd place.
<P>&gt; It is my honest opinion that ANY race can be king in any class,
<BR>&gt; and that the burden is on the skill of the player. Some classes
<BR>&gt; will never be able to hang 1v1, but will in the end have a use.
<BR>&gt; Example: Rogue gets destroyed 1v1 by just about any casting
<BR>&gt; class, but in a group fight with backstab shows his value. A
<BR>&gt; rogue at level 20 can deal out some pretty sweet damage between
<BR>&gt; backstab and dual weild in a group. The PvP server is about
<BR>&gt; group battles after all not a bunch of duels. If you wanna duel
<BR>&gt; you can do that on the regular servers. We need to be gearing
<BR>&gt; our class/race selections to group situations not 1v1 tests of
<BR>&gt; individual egos.
<P>&gt; Just my humble opinion. Hope to see you all on the
<BR>&gt; battlefeild!!!
<P>&gt; Angus The Grim[CC]
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
